The paper focuses on developing a comprehensive graph neural network system that can efficiently support various business scenarios, including product recommendation and personalized search. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which is concerned with the development of algorithms and models that can learn from data. The paper also discusses the challenges of providing efficient graph storage and computation capabilities, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DB (Databases) or cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Additionally, the paper proposes novel caching strategies and runtime improvements, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
